'''階級歧視'''（{{lang-en|Class discrimination}}）也称为'''階級主义'''（{{lang|en|Classism}}）是指建基於[[社會階級|社會階級]]的[[偏見|偏見]]和[[歧視|歧視]]。一切以犧牲[[下層階級|下層階級]]的利益，來滿足[[上層階級|上層階級]]的行為、態度、政治體系皆可歸入階級歧視當中<ref name=Kadi>{{cite book|last=Kadi|first=Joanna|title=Thinking Class|publisher=South End Press|year=1996|url=https://archive.org/details/thinkingclassske00kadi|isbn=0-89608-548-1}}</ref>。

== 歷史 ==
前農業社會的階級結構相對簡單，但到了出現餘糧的農業文明，則變得更為複雜<ref>{{cite book|title=A Brief History of the World Course No. 8080 [Audio CD]|author=Peter N. Stearns (Narrator)|publisher=The Teaching Company|asin=B000W595CC}}</ref>。自18世紀開始，階級歧視便已成為人們日常的一部分<ref>{{cite book|last1=Young|first1=Serinity|title=Encyclopedia of Women and World Religion|date=1999|publisher=Macmillan|isbn=0028648609|page=181|author2=Katie Cannon|editor=Serinity Young|format=Print|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RYgYAAAAIAAJ}}</ref>。

當代的階級歧視较难识别，因為階級結構已不再像以前般那麼僵化。心理學家托马斯·富勒-罗威尔（Thomas Fuller-Rowell）表示：[[阶级|阶级]]歧视的经历往往是較為含蓄不明顯的，很多受害者並不了解受到差別對待的真正原因」{{r|APS}}。

==跟其他制度的關係==
{{世界观|章节|time=2020-09-01|area=美国}}
在美國，已有廣泛研究顯示學業環境當中出現了社經、種族、性別不平等的情況，不過這些因素會如何影響學童在學業或非學業上的表現則尚未明瞭<ref>{{cite journal|last=Bécares|first=Laia|last2=Priest|first2=Naomi|date=2015-10-27|title=Understanding the Influence of Race/Ethnicity, Gender, and Class on Inequalities in Academic and Non-Academic Outcomes among Eighth-Grade Students: Findings from an Intersectionality Approach|url=http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0141363|journal=PLOS ONE|volume=10|issue=10|pages=e0141363|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0141363|issn=1932-6203|pmc=4624767|pmid=26505623|access-date=2020-09-21|archive-date=2018-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807064511/http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0141363|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 結構性歧視和個人歧視 ==
階級歧視除了涵蓋某人對於下層階級的歧視之外，還可以指一切擁有此一目的的結構性歧視，這類似於[[种族主义|种族主义]]一詞的字意。結構性階級歧視指的是「在……社会的各种制度當中，有意或无意地表露出階級歧視的一切表現」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gustavus.edu/reslife/documents/Classism.doc|title=Classism Definitions|website=gustavus.edu|accessdate=2018-03-18|archive-date=2016-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313231751/https://gustavus.edu/reslife/documents/Classism.doc|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

人与人之间的社会地位差异就像社會階級般，一樣會影響他們如何對待或看待彼此。地位较高的人較少與較低者混在一起，且他們往往較能夠透過影響法律和社會標準，來控制他人的活動<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/social-sciences/news-wires-white-papers-and-books/social-class-prejudice|title=Social Class Prejudice|website=Encyclopedia.com|access-date=2019-01-08|archive-date=2019-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327222511/https://www.encyclopedia.com/social-sciences/news-wires-white-papers-and-books/social-class-prejudice|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

個人歧視的同義詞有人際歧視、態度歧視、態度性歧視<ref>{{citation|last=Langhout|first=Regina Day|title=Assessing Classism in Academic Settings|date=2007|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/login?auth=0&type=summary&url=/journals/review_of_higher_education/v030/30.2langhout.html|last2=Rosselli|last3=Feinstein|first2=Francine|first3=Jonathan|journal=The Review of Higher Education|volume=30|issue=2|pages=145–184|doi=10.1353/rhe.2006.0073|accessdate=2020-09-21|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305034312/http://muse.jhu.edu/login?auth=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。美国杂志媒体协会（Association of Magazine Media）則把階級歧視定義為「任何按照收入、职业、教育和/或经济狀況，來把人放在下位的态度或制度」<ref>[http://www.magazine.org/diversity/managing/defining/8478.aspx "Glossary"].{{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309015508/http://www.magazine.org/diversity/managing/defining/8478.aspx|date=2012-03-09}}</ref>。

部分研究會把階級歧視分作個人歧視、結構歧視、文化歧視三類<ref>{{cite book|editor1-last=Adams|editor1-first=Maurianne|editor2-last=Bell|editor2-first=Lee Anne|editor3-last=Griffin|editor3-first=Pat|title=Teaching for Diversity and Social Justice|edition=2nd|publisher=Routledge|year=2007|page=317|url=https://books.google.com/?id=OI-5SlHR9PMC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|isbn=978-0-415-95199-9}}</ref>。

== 媒體上的階級歧視 ==
階級歧視可在電視節目、電影、社交媒體上表露出來。它是一種系統性現象<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gamble |first1=Matt |title=Classism: America's Overlooked Problem |url=https://www.therutgersreview.com/2018/02/10/classism-americas-overlooked-problem/ |website=The Rutgers Review |accessdate=2019-03-21 |archive-date=2019-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830162431/http://www.therutgersreview.com/2018/02/10/classism-americas-overlooked-problem/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而且人們經常忽略媒體對於階級歧視的影響。媒体反映了人們對階級歧視的所知所想。而大眾有機會受到當中的階級歧視理念影響，认为现实也是如此。儿童可以能從电影上接触到阶级歧视的觀念，繼而受到影響<ref>{{cite web |last1=Streib |first1=Jessi |title=Class Inequality in Children's Movies |url=https://classism.org/class-inequality-in-childrens-movies/ |website=Class Action |accessdate=2019-03-21 |archive-date=2019-03-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321213408/https://classism.org/class-inequality-in-childrens-movies/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Suttie |first1=Jill |title=How Adults Communicate Bias to Children |url=https://greatergood.berkeley.edu/article/item/how_adults_communicate_bias_to_children |accessdate=2019-03-21 |archive-date=2019-03-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321223415/https://greatergood.berkeley.edu/article/item/how_adults_communicate_bias_to_children |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在塑造人們对於某些群体的看法這件事上，媒体的角色舉足輕重<ref>{{cite web |last1=Burke |first1=Krista |title=Media Portrayal of Individuals in the Lower Class |url=https://digitalcommons.calpoly.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?referer=https://www.google.com/&httpsredir=1&article=1162&context=comssp |website=Digital Commons |accessdate=2019-03-21}}</ref>。民眾可以透過媒體接觸有關其他社會階級的資訊，或籍其影響其他人看待某個社會階級的方式<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.criticalmediaproject.org/cml/topicbackground/race-ethnicity/|title=Race & Ethnicity|website=criticalmediaproject.org|accessdate=2018-03-18|archive-date=2018-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180202160013/http://criticalmediaproject.org/cml/topicbackground/race-ethnicity/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.harvard.edu/andresmh/2013/04/classism-accountability-and-social-media/|title=Classism, Accountability, and Social Media|website=blogs.harvard.edu|accessdate=2018-03-18|archive-date=2018-12-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181213123706/https://blogs.harvard.edu/andresmh/2013/04/classism-accountability-and-social-media/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

